#week-title("One", "The Natal Chart as Alchemical Portrait")

=== Core Teaching

In Year Two, the astrological framework deepens. The natal chart is introduced
not as a predictive tool, but as an *alchemical map* of the individual — a
portrait of the practitioner's own elemental constitution.

Paracelsian alchemy holds that each person is born under a particular planetary
dominance. Your work as an alchemist is partly to bring the deficient planetary
forces within yourself into balance. A person strongly marked by Saturn may
excel in patience, but struggle with Mercurial flexibility. Your chart guides
you to what work is most essential for you personally.

=== Topics This Week

- The natal chart as an alchemical portrait
- Identifying planetary dominances and deficiencies
- Paracelsian constitutional balance
- The Mundane Chakra: planetary spheres as cosmic timing agents

#inner-work[
  *Casting the Chart*

  Obtain or cast your natal chart if you have not already done so. Identify your
  dominant planet(s) and the weakest represented planetary force.

  Journal on how this has shown up in your experience — in your life, and in your
  laboratory work. Are you drawn to specific herbs or operations that match your
  dominance, or do you avoid your deficiencies?
]

